   363‚ÜíRender the items as they become available. Filtering and sorting will happen automatically.
   364‚Üí
   365‚Üí```tsx
   366‚Üíconst [loading, setLoading] = React.useState(false)
   367‚Üíconst [items, setItems] = React.useState([])
   368‚Üí
   369‚ÜíReact.useEffect(() => {
   370‚Üí  async function getItems() {
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   397‚Üí### Use inside Popover
   399‚ÜíWe recommend using the [Radix UI popover](https://www.radix-ui.com/docs/primitives/components/popover) component. ‚åòK relies on the Radix UI Dialog component, so this will reduce your bundle size a bit due to shared dependencies.
   400‚Üí
   401‚Üí```bash
   402‚Üí$ pnpm install @radix-ui/react-popover
   403‚Üí```
   404‚Üí
   405‚ÜíRender `Command` inside of the popover content:
   406‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   426‚Üí### Drop in stylesheets
   428‚ÜíYou can find global stylesheets to drop in as a starting point for styling. See [website/styles/cmdk](website/styles/cmdk) for examples.
   429‚Üí
   430‚Üí## FAQ
   432‚Üí**Accessible?** Yes. Labeling, aria attributes, and DOM ordering tested with Voice Over and Chrome DevTools. [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) composes an accessible Dialog implementation.
   433‚Üí
   434‚Üí**Virtualization?** No. Good performance up to 2,000-3,000 items, though. Read below to bring your own.
   435‚Üí
   436‚Üí**Filter/sort items manually?** Yes. Pass `shouldFilter={false}` to [Command](#command-cmdk-root). Better memory usage and performance. Bring your own virtualization this way.
   437‚Üí
   438‚Üí**React 18 safe?** Yes, required. Uses React 18 hooks like `useId` and `useSyncExternalStore`.
   439‚Üí
   440‚Üí**Unstyled?** Yes, use the listed CSS selectors.
   441‚Üí
   442‚Üí**Hydration mismatch?** No, likely a bug in your code. Ensure the `open` prop to `Command.Dialog` is `false` on the server.
   443‚Üí
   444‚Üí**React strict mode safe?** Yes. Open an issue if you notice an issue.
   445‚Üí
   446‚Üí**Weird/wrong behavior?** Make sure your `Command.Item` has a `key` and unique `value`.
   447‚Üí
   448‚Üí**Concurrent mode safe?** Maybe, but concurrent mode is not yet real. Uses risky approaches like manual DOM ordering.
   449‚Üí
   450‚Üí**React server component?** No, it's a client component.
   451‚Üí
   452‚Üí**Listen for ‚åòK automatically?** No, do it yourself to have full control over keybind context.
   453‚Üí
   454‚Üí**React Native?** No, and no plans to support it. If you build a React Native version, let us know and we'll link your repository here.
   455‚Üí
   456‚Üí## History
   458‚ÜíWritten in 2019 by Paco ([@pacocoursey](https://twitter.com/pacocoursey)) to see if a composable combobox API was possible. Used for the Vercel command menu and autocomplete by Rauno ([@raunofreiberg](https://twitter.com/raunofreiberg)) in 2020. Re-written independently in 2022 with a simpler and more performant approach. Ideas and help from Shu ([@shuding\_](https://twitter.com/shuding_)).
   459‚Üí
   460‚Üí[use-descendants](https://github.com/pacocoursey/use-descendants) was extracted from the 2019 version.
   461‚Üí
   462‚Üí## Testing
   464‚ÜíFirst, install dependencies and Playwright browsers:
   465‚Üí
   466‚Üí```bash
   467‚Üípnpm install
   468‚Üípnpm playwright install
   469‚Üí```
   470‚Üí
   471‚ÜíThen ensure you've built the library:
   472‚Üí
   473‚Üí```bash
   474‚Üípnpm build
   475‚Üí```
   476‚Üí
   477‚ÜíThen run the tests using your local build against real browser engines:
   478‚Üí
   479‚Üí```bash
   480‚Üípnpm test
   481‚Üí```
cmdk/src/command-score.ts
    54‚Üífunction commandScoreInner(
    55‚Üí  string,
    56‚Üí  abbreviation,
    57‚Üí  lowerString,
    58‚Üí  lowerAbbreviation,
    59‚Üí  stringIndex,
    60‚Üí  abbreviationIndex,
    61‚Üí  memoizedResults,
    62‚Üí) {
    63‚Üí  if (abbreviationIndex === abbreviation.length) {
    64‚Üí    if (stringIndex === string.length) {
    65‚Üí      return SCORE_CONTINUE_MATCH
    66‚Üí    }
    67‚Üí    return PENALTY_NOT_COMPLETE
    68‚Üí  }
    69‚Üí
    70‚Üí  var memoizeKey = `${stringIndex},${abbreviationIndex}`
    71‚Üí  if (memoizedResults[memoizeKey] !== undefined) {
    72‚Üí    return memoizedResults[memoizeKey]
    73‚Üí  }
    74‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   150‚Üífunction formatInput(string) {
   151‚Üí  // convert all valid space characters to space so they match each other
   152‚Üí  return string.toLowerCase().replace(COUNT_SPACE_REGEXP, ' ')
   153‚Üí}
   155‚Üíexport function commandScore(string: string, abbreviation: string, aliases: string[]): number {
   156‚Üí  /* NOTE:
   157‚Üí   * in the original, we used to do the lower-casing on each recursive call, but this meant that toLowerCase()
   158‚Üí   * was the dominating cost in the algorithm, passing both is a little ugly, but considerably faster.
   159‚Üí   */
   160‚Üí  string = aliases && aliases.length > 0 ? `${string + ' ' + aliases.join(' ')}` : string
   161‚Üí  return commandScoreInner(string, abbreviation, formatInput(string), formatInput(abbreviation), 0, 0, {})
   162‚Üí}
